HEADWORD: Supraspinous
<hw>Su`pra*spi"nous</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Situated
above a spine or spines; especially, situated above, or on the dorsal
side of, the neural spines of the vertebral column, or above, or in
front of, the spine of the scapula.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

